### Infrastructure: Connecting the City

#### Transportation Networks

For commercial air travel, residents of Pembroke Pines primarily utilize the nearby [Fort Lauderdale–Hollywood International Airport](/Fort_Lauderdale%E2%80%93Hollywood_International_Airport) and [Miami International Airport](/Miami_International_Airport). The city itself maintains [North Perry Airport](/North_Perry_Airport), a general aviation facility under the purview of the Broward County Aviation Department.

Public transportation within Pembroke Pines is facilitated by [Broward County Transit](/Broward_County_Transit), with the city collaborating to offer additional intra-city routes.

Key expressways serving the area include [Interstate 75](/Interstate_75_in_Florida) and [Florida's Turnpike](/Florida%27s_Turnpike) (SR 91). Major arterial roads include [U.S. 27](/U.S._Route_27_in_Florida), [University Drive](/Florida_State_Road_817), [Pines Boulevard](/Florida_State_Road_820), [Sheridan Street](/Florida_State_Road_822), [Flamingo Road](/Florida_State_Road_823), and [Pembroke Road](/Florida_State_Road_824).

The street grid in Pembroke Pines is an extension of that found in neighboring Hollywood, with streets identified by adding a 'west' designation to the cardinal direction. Streets north of Pines Boulevard are designated 'northwest,' while those south are designated 'southwest.'

